commentary: Stoinis to Dhawan, 1 run Dhawan is on 99. Dhawan is nervous. There's a mix-up between the wickets, and there's a direct hit. Kohli dishes out a full-stretch dive at the non-striker's end and is safe. Kohli and Dhawan exchange wry smiles. Then comes Dhawan's trademark celebration. He has his hands aloft, bat raised, and acknowledges the cheers. His coach Shastri is on his feet in the dressing room applauding Dhawan. Very full on off, jabbed to mid-off. Yes-no, yes-no, Dhawan somehow gets a single in the end and reaches a hundred - his sixth at an ICC ODI tournament. Only Tendulkar and Ganguly are ahead of him on this list

commentary: Pandya to Warner, 1 run, OUT Is Finch gone! He's walking even before the decision is given by the third umpire! This was a length ball outside off, and Warner struck it to Jadhav at deep point. He picked the ball up in a flash, and a bit of hesitation on the second run has cost the captain his wicket. Good throw from the deep, and Hardik was composed to collect the ball and break the stumps. Oh dear. Wonder who among the two batsmen called for the second run

commentary: Chahal to Smith, no run another Dhoni special! Is Smith run out? This was full outside off, and Smith came down the wicket to whip it away. The shot was inside-edged onto his pads and then rolled towards Dhoni, and the keeper threw the balls at the stumps. But replays show that Smith had managed to bring his bat back in before the bails were dislodged Azhar: 'It's more like a T20 match now.. 198 needed of 20 overs.. Though it's a bit harder for aussies as they ve lost both their openers'

Though it's a bit harder for aussies as they ve lost both their openers'
